TY  - JOUR
T1  - Note—Can a Reduction in Set Up Costs Indeed Increase Total Costs?
AU  - Gerchak, Yigal
Y1  - 1988/10/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.34.10.1271
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.34.10.1271
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1271
EP  - 1272
VL  - 34
IS  - 10
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Zangwill (Zangwill, W. I. 1987. From EOQ towards ZI. Management Sci. 33 1209?1223.) has constructed an example which purports to show that reducing set up costs can increase total cost. We show that this happened as a result of restricting the policies to be of a ?greedy? nature. The expected cost of truly optimal policies is shown not to increase.
AB  - Zangwill (Zangwill, W. I. 1987. From EOQ towards ZI. Management Sci. 33 1209?1223.) has constructed an example which purports to show that reducing set up costs can increase total cost. We show that this happened as a result of restricting the policies to be of a ?greedy? nature. The expected cost of truly optimal policies is shown not to increase.
